issue.title: Problem with aws s3 connection.

repository.name: diffgram
repository.description: Training Data (Annotation, Catalog, Workflow) for all Data Types (Image, Video, 3D, Text, Geo, Audio, more) at scale.

issue.body:
Hi all,

I have an issue when  I trying to connect with s3 to upload my dataset. I already have all permissions (fullS3Access). But still facing this error:

{'status_text': 'Exceeded retry limit, no valid response'}.


![cap](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58047828/126197122-dd73d567-a195-4ade-b30c-9b32c03f9549.png)

Would you please help me with this problem?

body:
Hi @cvm-int,

This is problem looks like a connection pool issue on your DB. The Walrus currently uses up to 8 threads and if all are working for pronlonged times it can take up all default connection.

In release 0.7.8: https://github.com/diffgram/diffgram/releases/tag/0.7.8

We've added the `DATABASE_CONNECTION_POOL_SIZE` to increase the default number of connection available. You can set it on the `.env` file in your diffgram folder and then recreate the containers to get the number of connections up. 

We will work on adding a setting to tweak the number of threads that process images in case you needed less to keep connection pool smaller.

Let me know if this helps!

Thanks for answering.

Hi @cvm-int !

Did you change the value of `DATABASE_CONNECTION_POOL_SIZE`, what value did you set it to?

Make sure you check this: https://diffgram.readme.io/docs/open-core-docker-install-cheatsheet

to learn how to setup the variable value correctly and update diffgram with docker compose

en your .env file You can try adding: 

`DATABASE_CONNECTION_POOL_SIZE=20`

for example, to increase max connections to 20 and retry to see if error stops showing.

I followed the cheetsheet steps and set DATABASE_CONNECTION_POOL_SIZE=20 and started ok but then it returned the same error. Now I set DATABASE_CONNECTION_POOL_SIZE=40  and keeps running without the previous error (Thanks!!).

Glad the connection pool error is gone. We'll try to identify ways to reduce the number of connections overall. 

As for the `Error sending to Diffgram Eventhub` for now its should not interfere with your uploads, we'll work on seeing the cause of this error as it's related to one of our external monitoring services and not so much to the upload.

Let me know if you have any other questions, otherwise we can proceed to close this issue
Ok, thanks for your quick support ⚡. This issue can be closed.
Sounds good :) Glad we could help! @cvm-int

issue.title: Long term sync from Dataset to task not working

repository.name: diffgram
repository.description: Training Data (Annotation, Catalog, Workflow) for all Data Types (Image, Video, 3D, Text, Geo, Audio, more) at scale.

issue.body:
A Task was created related to a Dataset but when more files were imported to the Dataset, the number of files in task did not increased. 

Task was created with long term sync (see screenshot attached). Dataset currently has 17, 919 but task has 17, 617.
I will appreciate your kind support on this issue.
